read map in order:
a=2 ‚Üí skip
b=2 ‚Üí skip
c=1 ‚Üí first with count 1 ‚úì

return 'c' ‚úÖ

Problem 3 ‚Äî Anagram Check
Question: are two strings anagrams of each other?
s = "listen"
t = "silent"
answer = true  (same characters, different order)
Two strings are anagrams if and only if they have the exact same character frequencies.
javapublic boolean isAnagram(String s, String t) {

    // different lengths ‚Äî impossible to be anagram
    if (s.length() != t.length()) return false;

    Map<Character, Integer> freq = new HashMap<>();

    // build map FROM s ‚Äî increment
    for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
        freq.put(c, freq.getOrDefault(c, 0) + 1);
    }

    // tear down map WITH t ‚Äî decrement
    for (char c : t.toCharArray()) {
        freq.put(c, freq.getOrDefault(c, 0) - 1);
    }

    // if any count is non-zero ‚Äî they had different frequencies
    for (int count : freq.values()) {
        if (count != 0) return false;
    }

    return true;
}
